§ Definition ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ Let $\eqc{(a, b)}, \eqc{(b, c)} ∈ 𝗤$. ⦉

  ‖ The ❬rational sum❭ of $\eqc{(a, b)}$ with $\eqc{(b, c)}$ is
    $\eqc{(ad + bc, bd)}$.
    † ⦊
      ‖ An account that this is well-defined will appear in
        future editions. ⦉
    ⦉⦉
⦉

§§ Notation ⦉
¶ ⦊
  ‖ We denote the rational sum of $q, r ∈ 𝗤$ by $q + r$. ⦉
